1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper introduces a novel layer named periodic convolution layer, which can be applied to problems related to computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper utilizes deep learning methods to estimate the band gap of materials. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for learning the periodicity behind the periodic table. 
4. cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper introduces a new method for handling inputs with periodicity, which may be applied to other problems related to time series. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper utilizes neural networks for estimating the band gap of materials.
